WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:01.067 --> 00:00:03.869
<i>I went on a journey and I
 went all over the Amazon</i>

00:00:03.869 --> 00:00:07.540
<i> to try and find out the
 truth about the Amazon.</i>

00:00:08.273 --> 00:00:10.709
<i>This idea of these nasty people</i>

00:00:10.709 --> 00:00:12.746
<i> destroying the Amazon,
 they're not.</i>

00:00:12.746 --> 00:00:15.048
<i> They are just people
 trying to make a living.</i>

00:00:15.048 --> 00:00:18.584
<i> And what I saw was this
 endless poverty trap.</i>

00:00:18.584 --> 00:00:20.853 line:0%
( audience applause )

00:00:20.853 --> 00:00:22.221 line:0%
<i> Three years ago now,</i>

00:00:22.221 --> 00:00:25.658
<i> I'd bought an illegal
coca plantation by mistake.</i>

00:00:25.658 --> 00:00:27.793
<i>These are raw coca leaves.</i>

00:00:27.793 --> 00:00:29.462
<i> They have the highest
 alkaloid content</i>

00:00:29.462 --> 00:00:32.631
<i> of any coca leaves
 in the world.</i>

00:00:32.631 --> 00:00:35.101
Which means they make
really good cocaine.

00:00:35.535 --> 00:00:37.069
And they're mine.

00:00:37.069 --> 00:00:39.606
- ( audience laughter )
- ( Charlie laughs )

00:00:40.706 --> 00:00:44.076 line:0%
So, I became a coca lord
by mistake.

00:00:44.076 --> 00:00:45.377 line:0%
( audience laughter )

00:00:46.312 --> 00:00:50.983
<i>Now, I didn't mean to buy a
cocaine plantation, obviously.</i>

00:00:50.983 --> 00:00:52.418
<i>But, I bought it over the phone.</i>

00:00:52.418 --> 00:00:54.453
<i> A friend of mine phoned
 me up and he said</i>

00:00:54.453 --> 00:00:58.023
"There's this piece of land
at the end of a logging road

00:00:58.023 --> 00:01:01.093
and the head of the National
Park needs someone to buy it.

00:01:01.093 --> 00:01:04.463
The illegal loggers are
going up this track

00:01:04.463 --> 00:01:05.498
they're going through the land

00:01:05.598 --> 00:01:07.900
and into the National Park
to cut the hardwood trees.

00:01:07.900 --> 00:01:10.670
And if someone can buy
that piece of land

00:01:10.670 --> 00:01:13.239
we stand a chance of
protecting that part

00:01:13.239 --> 00:01:15.541
of Manu National Park."

00:01:15.541 --> 00:01:17.043
But, what I actually got

00:01:17.043 --> 00:01:18.110
you know, when I got there

00:01:18.110 --> 00:01:20.646
and saw it several months
later was, you know

00:01:20.646 --> 00:01:23.849
hundred acres of severely
degraded secondary rainforest.

00:01:24.416 --> 00:01:26.886
And two hectares
of illegal coke.

00:01:26.886 --> 00:01:29.222
I also got an illegal
logging camp

00:01:29.889 --> 00:01:32.525
with an illegal
logger living in it.

00:01:33.492 --> 00:01:35.495
<i> That's Elias there,
 on the right.</i>

00:01:35.495 --> 00:01:38.965
<i>I bought the land off Tito,
his dad here on the left.</i>

00:01:38.965 --> 00:01:42.869
And Elias was one of
the most infamous

00:01:42.869 --> 00:01:45.972
notorious, illegal
loggers in the area.

00:01:45.972 --> 00:01:48.507
The National Parks hated him,
he was a thief

00:01:48.507 --> 00:01:50.743
he was a liar, he was
this, he was that.

00:01:51.243 --> 00:01:53.746
And as a result, I was
absolutely terrified of him.

00:01:53.746 --> 00:01:57.617
He was so muscly. I've never
seen a human being...

00:01:57.617 --> 00:01:59.985
You can't kind of get it
from that picture, but yeah.

00:01:59.985 --> 00:02:01.454
Anyway, I was terrified of him.

00:02:03.289 --> 00:02:07.060
And I would... camped on the
land when I first went there

00:02:07.060 --> 00:02:09.461
and I'd lie down, I could
hear the chainsaws at night

00:02:09.461 --> 00:02:10.496
and I'd come out in the morning

00:02:10.496 --> 00:02:12.398
and there'd be a massive
pile of hardwood

00:02:12.398 --> 00:02:14.100
in the driveway to my land.

00:02:14.100 --> 00:02:16.202
And then, two hours later,
it had gone.

00:02:16.202 --> 00:02:19.238
This kind of went on, it
went on and then one day...

00:02:20.039 --> 00:02:23.142
So, we were filming this as
a part of a TV documentary

00:02:23.142 --> 00:02:25.745
and Gavin,
the director said to me

00:02:25.745 --> 00:02:27.546
"You know, you've really
gotta go meet this guy."

00:02:27.546 --> 00:02:29.982
And I said,
"I'm scared. I don't want to."

00:02:30.649 --> 00:02:32.652
And I talked to National Parks,
one of them actually said

00:02:32.652 --> 00:02:35.354
"You've bought the most
dangerous piece of land

00:02:35.354 --> 00:02:37.156
off the most dangerous family

00:02:37.156 --> 00:02:39.825
in the most dangerous
part of Southern Peru."

00:02:39.825 --> 00:02:43.062
And, you know, that scared
the hell out of me.

00:02:43.062 --> 00:02:44.230
And I'm camping on it.

00:02:44.230 --> 00:02:45.965
( audience laughter )

00:02:45.965 --> 00:02:48.534
And a few years earlier,
in exactly the same spot

00:02:48.534 --> 00:02:50.470
where I was camping, a
group of geologists

00:02:50.470 --> 00:02:53.606
had been basically, held
up with guns and robbed.

00:02:53.606 --> 00:02:55.707
It was a... scary prospect.

00:02:55.707 --> 00:02:57.343
So, I didn't want to meet Elias.

00:02:57.910 --> 00:02:59.579
Anyway, Gavin said,
"You're gonna have to."

00:02:59.579 --> 00:03:00.947
and he forced me to do it.

00:03:00.947 --> 00:03:02.214
So, we marched
through the forest.

00:03:02.214 --> 00:03:04.817
And I tracked Elias, he's
really hard to find.

00:03:04.817 --> 00:03:07.052
I tracked him through--
I could find wet footprints.

00:03:07.052 --> 00:03:08.187
We did this for about an hour

00:03:08.187 --> 00:03:09.589
and eventually
I heard a chainsaw.

00:03:10.690 --> 00:03:13.226
And basically, I
doorstepped this man

00:03:13.226 --> 00:03:16.095
in the middle of cutting a tree
down, with a whole film crew.

00:03:16.462 --> 00:03:18.497
And it was a really
weird moment because

00:03:18.497 --> 00:03:20.766
he was like,
"What the hell is going on?"

00:03:20.766 --> 00:03:22.702
You know, really remote
part of the Amazon

00:03:22.702 --> 00:03:25.504
this bloke turns up with a
boom pole and a camera.

00:03:25.504 --> 00:03:27.206
- ( Charlie laughs )
- ( audience laughter )

00:03:27.206 --> 00:03:28.975
Anyway, he's not going
to attack us, is he?

00:03:29.475 --> 00:03:32.178
Anyway, we sat down and
we hung out and...

00:03:32.178 --> 00:03:34.714
I basically said
"You gotta leave.

00:03:34.714 --> 00:03:37.916
You know, it's not working.
You can't stay on this land.

00:03:37.916 --> 00:03:39.918
You are the bad illegal logger.

00:03:39.918 --> 00:03:42.221
I don't want you on this land,
you're gonna have to leave."

00:03:42.988 --> 00:03:47.727
And he spun me this line about
how he had a disabled daughter

00:03:47.727 --> 00:03:51.964
and it's all he could do,
you know, to survive and...

00:03:52.698 --> 00:03:55.001
keep her, and you know
keep his family alive.

00:03:55.001 --> 00:03:56.469
And you know, I
didn't believe him.

00:03:57.236 --> 00:03:58.370
So, I'm gonna show you this now.

