So, I went on a journey

00:06:47.639 --> 00:06:50.809
to find out the truth
about the Amazon

00:06:50.809 --> 00:06:53.679
trying to find out how can
we tackle these problems.

00:06:53.679 --> 00:06:56.749
And we can tackle them
by understanding them.

00:06:56.749 --> 00:06:59.218
So, I went on a kind of
journey of understanding.

00:06:59.218 --> 00:07:00.886
<i> This is Erasmus.</i>

00:07:00.886 --> 00:07:06.726
<i> He's one of 35,000 gold
 miners in Southern Peru.</i>

00:07:06.726 --> 00:07:10.797
<i>The gold mining is a huge
 environmental problem.</i>

00:07:10.797 --> 00:07:14.200
<i> You know, this is like a
 modern day gold rush.</i>

00:07:14.200 --> 00:07:16.035
<i> But, these guys
 are chasing dust,</i>

00:07:16.035 --> 00:07:17.536
<i> they're not
 chasing nuggets.</i>

00:07:17.536 --> 00:07:22.241
And they use a whole load of
chemicals within that process

00:07:22.241 --> 00:07:24.376
Mercury particularly.

00:07:24.376 --> 00:07:26.879
If I give you a sense
of scale there.

00:07:27.980 --> 00:07:30.716
There's a truck.
That dot there.

00:07:31.250 --> 00:07:33.385
<i>When you see that, you start
 realizing how big it is.</i>

00:07:33.385 --> 00:07:37.490
<i>There's whole towns have cropped
 up to supply this trade.</i>

00:07:37.757 --> 00:07:39.591
<i> And towns of
 thousands of people.</i>

00:07:39.591 --> 00:07:40.793
There's prostitution,

00:07:40.793 --> 00:07:43.295
there's human trafficking,
there's crime.

00:07:43.295 --> 00:07:46.765
And you know, it's a horrible
modern day gold rush.

00:07:46.765 --> 00:07:51.136
<i> So, I went to work with
Erasmus on his gold mine.</i>

00:07:51.136 --> 00:07:52.472
<i> This is one day,
 they got--</i>

00:07:52.472 --> 00:07:55.541
<i> This is six and a half
 grams of 24 karat gold.</i>

00:07:56.008 --> 00:07:58.544
That's worth about $190 bucks.

